        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Mesopotamian pottery styles [300107735], Mesopotamian (culture or style) [300019828], Near Eastern (Early Western World) [300019571], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the pottery style found in the Diyala region of Mesopotamia and characterized by generally large, broad-shouldered pots with painted red designs, outlined in black, on a buff or yellow ground.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050633/Frankfort, Art and Architecture of the Ancient Orient (1970)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica encontrado predominantemente en la región de Diyala de Mesopotamia a principios del período Dinástico Temprano de aproximadamente 2900 al 2750 a.C. El estilo se caracteriza por vasijas generalmente grandes, de hombros anchos con diseños pintados en rojo, de contorno en negro, sobre una base beige o amarilla.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar een aardewerkstijl die voornamelijk werd gevonden in de regio Diyala in Mesopotamië, aan het begin van de vroegdynastische periode van circa 2900 tot 2750 v. Chr. De stijl wordt gekarakteriseerd door voornamelijk grote, breedgeschouderde potten, beschilderd met rode, zwart omlijnde figuren, tegen een vaalgele of gele achtergrond.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指於西元前2900年至西元前2750年間的早王朝開始，流行於美索不達米亞的迪亞拉一地的陶器風格。此風格的特色為寬肩的大型陶罐，並於牛皮色或黃色陶身上繪有以黑色勾勒出輪廓線的紅色設計圖案。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
